The final conservative-amplitude cohort is still running cleanly. Because stage 0 has zero obstacles, any collision count above zero would indicate an accounting/setup error; the completed checkpoint cohort from the prior identical run had exactly 0 collisions and 50/50 timeouts, so the remaining uncertainty is the scripted success fraction and its velocity profile.
